<book>
<page type="intro">
<text>Materials - Alien Edition
A Guide to Material Properties

By Ayumu Nagasawa</text>
</page>

<page type="text">
<text>Upon landing on the alien world, many new materials have been doscovered. From samples of the metals themselves, scanner readings, and reasonable extrapolation, we have formed statistics for these newer materials. This is the first time these material properties have seen publication.</text>
</page>

<page type="sectionpage">
<title>Material Traits</title>
<text>Some materials have traits that augment their natural uses.

- Reinforced: 10% chance per level of not using durability
- Stonebound: The tool mines faster as it wears out, but does less damage
- Jagged: The tool does more damage as it wears out, but mines slower
- Writable: One extra modifier per piece
- Tasty: Sometimes drops food items</text>
</page>

<page type="sectionpage">
<title>Material Statistics:</title>
<text>Materials have more possible attributes than 
when Skyla wrote his seminal work.

- Harvest Difficulty: What tool level is needed 
  to mine it.
- Harvest level: The maximum hardness a tool
  can mine.
- Durability: How many times the material can 
  be used before breaking.
- Handle Mod: Tools with this as a handle 
  multiply their durability by this amount.
- Mining Speed: How quickly the tool mines 
  materials it is effective against.
- Attack Damage: How much extra damage this 
  tool does when attacking
- XP Required: How much XP this material 
  requires to level up.</text>
</page>

